{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2020-06-15-14-22-debugging-and-docker-compose/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"ohmybuck"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"1cb66ff2-dc4f-511c-9891-1934b3e9b128","excerpt":"Debugging python libraries inside a running docker container","html":"<p>Debugging python libraries inside a running docker container</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token comment\"># Find the running process</span>\ndocker <span class=\"token function\">ps</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Execute a command inside the container</span>\ndocker <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">exec</span> -it <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>container ID<span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token function\">bash</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Install an editor if none available</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">apt-get</span> update <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"token function\">apt-get</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> -y <span class=\"token function\">vim</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Edit the library</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">vim</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>file<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Debugging And Docker Compose","date":"June 15, 2020","description":"Debugging And Docker Compose"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2020-06-15-14-22-debugging-and-docker-compose/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2020-06-08-09-41-setting-up-your-mac/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Setting Up Your Mac","draft":null}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2020-06-20-15-22-setting-up-for-clojurescript/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Setting up for ClojureScript","draft":null}}}}}